[Amit Varma]: to sort of disengage from something if it is not working, or I'm not loving it so much.

01:03:07.200 --> 01:03:12.280
[Amit Varma]: So it's not like I go all in on every single thing that I do. But when I'm enjoying something

01:03:12.280 --> 01:03:17.680
[Amit Varma]: like you know, like India Uncut or back when I was blogging regularly, or the scene in

01:03:17.680 --> 01:03:22.400
[Amit Varma]: the unseen or poker, I'll just go all in. But the regret is that the you know, the going

01:03:22.400 --> 01:03:26.520
[Amit Varma]: all in comes at the expense of something which is, in my case, it's a writing of books like

01:03:26.520 --> 01:03:31.360
[Amit Varma]: pre poker, I don't really regret the very meandering journey I took because I don't

01:03:31.360 --> 01:03:38.200
[Amit Varma]: think I had the life experience or the maturity to be able to write good books anyway. But

