[Amit Varma]: I don't need to sell you on the power of podcasting. Audio is a unique medium different

02:42:45.520 --> 02:42:50.320
[Amit Varma]: from any other. And it allows for a level of depth and engagement that no other form does.

02:42:50.320 --> 02:42:54.800
[Amit Varma]: You've no doubt experienced this in the long form conversations that I've had here.

02:42:54.800 --> 02:43:00.640
[Amit Varma]: But even for storytellers, this is the most exciting medium. And the best part of it all is

02:43:00.640 --> 02:43:06.560
[Amit Varma]: anyone can start a podcast, you are limited only by your imagination and desire. And I want to

02:43:06.560 --> 02:43:11.600
[Amit Varma]: help you by sharing my insights with you. I've just launched an online course called the art

02:43:11.600 --> 02:43:17.360
[Amit Varma]: of podcasting, in which I will talk about what makes audio so unique, the different forms of

02:43:17.360 --> 02:43:22.480
[Amit Varma]: storytelling that it enables the art of the interview, and what will make your podcast

02:43:22.480 --> 02:43:27.680
[Amit Varma]: stand out. I'll talk about these broader concepts, as well as the nitty gritties of what equipment to

02:43:27.680 --> 02:43:32.960
[Amit Varma]: use how to record how to distribute how to market your podcast and build your brand.

